0:{"rsc":["$","$1","c",{"children":[["$","article",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__articlePage","children":[["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"BlogPosting\",\"headline\":\"Small Deck, Big Impact: Smart Designs for Compact Backyards\",\"image\":[\"https://www.ldndecks.com/images/img20.jpeg\"],\"datePublished\":\"2026-04-21T04:00:00.000Z\",\"dateModified\":\"2026-04-21T04:00:00.000Z\",\"author\":[{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"Loudoun Decks Team\",\"url\":\"https://www.ldndecks.com\"}],\"publisher\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"Loudoun Decks\",\"url\":\"https://www.ldndecks.com\",\"logo\":{\"@type\":\"ImageObject\",\"url\":\"https://www.ldndecks.com/ldndecks-logo.webp\"}},\"description\":\"Space-saving furniture, multi-level layouts, and corner designs for small lots. Learn how to maximize your square footage in Northern Virginia.\",\"mainEntityOfPage\":{\"@type\":\"WebPage\",\"@id\":\"https://www.ldndecks.com/blog/small-deck-big-impact-designs\"},\"isAccessibleForFree\":true,\"inLanguage\":\"en-US\",\"speakable\":{\"@type\":\"SpeakableSpecification\",\"cssSelector\":[\".leadParagraph\",\"h1\",\"h2\"]}}"}}],["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__heroSection","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__imgWrapper","children":[["$","$L2",null,{"src":"/images/img20.jpeg","alt":"Small Deck, Big Impact: Smart Designs for Compact Backyards","fill":true,"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__heroImg","priority":true,"sizes":"100vw"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__imgOverlay","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__containerLarge","children":[["$","$L3",null,{"href":"/blog","className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__backLink","children":"← Back to News"}],["$","h1",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__title","children":"Small Deck, Big Impact: Smart Designs for Compact Backyards"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__meta","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__author","children":["By ","Loudoun Decks Team"]}],["$","span",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__divider","children":"•"}],["$","span",null,{"children":"April 21, 2026"}]]}]]}]}]]}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__contentSection","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__containerNarrow","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__contentBody","children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__leadParagraph","children":"Space-saving furniture, multi-level layouts, and corner designs for small lots. Learn how to maximize your square footage in Northern Virginia."}],[["$","p","0",{"children":"Not every Northern Virginia property has a sprawling acre of land. In towns like Reston, Ashburn, and Alexandria, backyards are often compact, requiring a surgical approach to deck design. A small deck doesn’t have to feel cramped; with the right architectural \"tricks,\" you can create an expansive-feeling retreat on a tiny footprint."}],["$","h2","1",{"style":{"marginTop":"40px","marginBottom":"20px","color":"#111"},"children":"1. The Power of the Corner Nook"}],["$","p","2",{"children":"When space is at a premium, we often leverage corner-oriented designs. By pushing the primary seating area into a corner of the yard and using the house wall as one side of the \"room,\" we open up the center of the yard for traffic flow. Built-in L-shaped benches are a massive space-saver here, as they provide seating for six adults while taking up zero room for chair legs."}],["$","h2","3",{"style":{"marginTop":"40px","marginBottom":"20px","color":"#111"},"children":"2. Multi-Level Zoning"}],"$L4","$L5","$L6"],"$L7"]}]}]}],"$L8"]}],["$L9"],"$La"]}],"isPartial":false,"staleTime":300,"varyParams":null,"buildId":"Jebrcr4Vyd2YosxlccnHN"}
4:["$","p","4",{"children":"If we can’t go wide, we go vertical. By introducing a small 7-inch step between two distinct zones, we create a psychological separation of space. The upper level near the kitchen becomes the \"Grill Zone,\" while the lower level, just a few feet away, becomes the \"Zen Nook.\" This subtle change in elevation stops the eye from seeing the deck as a single tiny rectangle and instead perceives it as an intricate, multi-room suite."}]
5:["$","h2","5",{"style":{"marginTop":"40px","marginBottom":"20px","color":"#111"},"children":"3. Sleek Railing Systems"}]
6:["$","p","6",{"children":"In a small space, heavy wood pickets feel like a cage. To make a small deck feel twice as large, we recommend low-profile railing systems like black aluminum or stainless steel cable. Because the human eye can see through these thin lines, the boundaries of the deck disappear, and your view extends all the way to the property line, making the deck feel much less enclosed."}]
7:["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__conclusionBox","children":[["$","h3",null,{"children":"Ready to upgrade your outdoor living space?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Contact Loudoun Decks today for a free estimate and planning consultation."}],["$","$L3",null,{"href":"/contact","className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__ctaBtn","children":"Get Started"}]]}]
